    <stitle>VT-365 Diesel Engine Diagnostics (2002) - HARD START AND NO START DIAGNOSTICS - Test Procedures - Main Power
        Relay Voltage to IDM
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="3">
        <title>Main Power Relay Voltage to IDM</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <figure id="f2400543" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D3167.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Purpose</emph>
            </para>
            <para>To determine correct power supplied to operate the IDM. The IDM requires 7 volts minimum to operate
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Tools</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Relay breakout harness</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>DMM</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, read all
                        safety instructions in the foreword of this manual. Follow all warnings, cautions, and notes.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Batteries must be fully charged before doing the following procedures.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Voltage Measurement with Breakout Harness at Main Power Relay</title>
            <figure id="f2400544" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D3121.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Relay breakout harness installed</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn all accessories off.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install relay breakout harness between IDM power relay and power distribution box.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect DMM POS to lead 87 and NEG to ground post on cowl.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Crank engine for 20 seconds and measure voltage.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Record the lowest voltage on Hard Start and No Start Diagnostics form.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>If the voltage is below 7 volts, the IDM power relay may be resetting, resulting from low
                            voltage and current from the batteries or problems in the ignition circuit or power feed
                            circuits. See Injector Drive Module Power (IDM PWR) in Section 7.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Low battery voltage: failed batteries, high resistance at battery cable connections or in
                        wiring to the IDM
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Low or no battery voltage to the IDM: high resistance or an open power feed circuit to the IDM
                        or IDM power relay. The IDM power circuit fuse in battery box may be open, or the IDM power
                        relay may be defective.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>V
                        <subscript>IGN</subscript>
                        circuit problem
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Defective IDM</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Voltage Measurement at 12 Pin Connection with Breakout harness</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Tools</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>12 way breakout harness</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>DMM</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn off all accessories.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect 12 Pin connector at IDM.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2400545" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D31156.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>12 Pin breakout harness installed</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install 12 pin breakout harness between both connectors.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect leads of the DMM to each of the following test points:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>POS 9 to NEG 8 ( V
                            <subscript>IGN</subscript>
                            and MPR)
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>POS 12 to NEG 1 (IDM Pwr-)</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>POS 6 to NEG 1 ( IDM Pwr and Logic power)</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Crank engine for 20 seconds and measure voltage.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Record the lowest voltage on Hard Start and No Start Diagnostics form .</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>If the voltage is below 7 volts, the IDM power relay may be resetting, resulting from low
                            voltage and current from the batteries or problems in the ignition circuit power feed
                            circuits. See Injector Drive Module Power (IDM PWR) in Section 7.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
